.TH PRODBOX_cluster 1
.SH NAME
prodbox-cluster \- Local cluster lifecycle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prodbox cluster
.SH DESCRIPTION
Local Kubernetes cluster lifecycle. AWS-free: every command here decodes config and runs with an empty aws.* block. Public DNS + TLS lives under `prodbox edge`.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Check cluster and Vault status
.TP
\fBhealth\fR
Check Kubernetes health
.TP
\fBstart\fR
Start the cluster service
.TP
\fBstop\fR
Stop the cluster service
.TP
\fBrestart\fR
Restart the cluster service
.TP
\fBreconcile\fR
Reconcile the local cluster
.TP
\fBdelete\fR
Delete the local cluster
.TP
\fBlogs\fR
Show cluster service logs
.TP
\fBfederation\fR
Downstream cluster custody
.TP
\fBwait\fR
Wait for deployments to be ready
.TP
\fBworkload-logs\fR
Show recent workload logs
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBprodbox cluster reconcile\fR
Reconcile the supported local cluster state.
